I need to get my 49th lvl Fire pet.  Earth pet takes too long.  <br>
<br>
I break the spawns by running into aggro range and running out real quick.  This means you are on the aggro list of the creature but you don't have a single point on you so the MoBs will immediately get on your pet.  If you stay at max heal range you should be fine while your pet solo's them (heals will put you on their aggro list with points).   You'll take a couple of hits this way but with the phantom armor regen that isn't a big deal.   As far as I can tell this is the safest way to break a 2 spawn without getting one aggro'd on you. (And bloodgills are a bitch if one comes after you.. they bash like mad and its tough to channel through them.. and since JBoots/SoW does you no good underwater you aren't going to outrun them.. )<br>
<br>
Once I have them broken I keep them broken by running to the spawn spot and having my pet guard the spot in between where they spawn.  This allows me to read a book or do whatever and as soon as one pops my pet is on it (and I'll hear this and know to go over and give them a blast or two).   <br>
<br>
You can get to 50th in no time doing BG's.   Experience is actually better in a group.. a Magician and Enchanter can easily outpace the spawns.. add in a third and you can pull top ledge and the bottom all in a rotation with minimal downtime.  <br>
<br>
The most I've been able to keep up with solo is 3 of the ledge spots using at least one 600pt blast per BG (usually one 600pt and one 176pt though).  Without clarity I think tying to do all 4 would be tough to keep them split up-- but probably possible with the 49th lvl Fire Pet since you could take breaks during some to med and let your pet solo.   <p> <br>
